{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\nFor an additive map the two signers must write distinct, self-identifying keys, and\ncompletion validity needs a material fingerprint to detect post-signing edits.\n## What\nBoth sign sites set an unsigned `data[\"kind\"]` on the `SIGNATURE` event (`plan-review`,\n`completion-verifier`) for robust routing (kind stays anchored via `manifest[0]`). The\ncompletion signer ALSO records the plan-review material fingerprint\n(description/AC/file_impact/children) as a manifest line, so completion validity-on-read can\nrecompute and compare (symmetric with plan-review). Drift-refresh re-sign preserves kind.\n## Scope\n`src/rebar/llm/plan_review/attest.py` (`sign_plan_review`, `refresh_attestation`),\n`src/rebar/_commands/transition.py` (`_verdict_manifest` + completion signing),\n`src/rebar/signing.py` (kind passthrough if needed).\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Plan-review SIGNATURE events carry `data[\"kind\"]==\"plan-review\"`.\n- [ ] Completion SIGNATURE events carry `data[\"kind\"]==\"completion-verifier\"`.\n- [ ] Completion manifest records the material fingerprint (legacy completion sigs without it are treated as material-unknown by validity-on-read).\n- [ ] `data[\"kind\"]` and the fingerprint line do NOT alter the existing canonical payload in a way that breaks old signatures (no PAYLOAD_VERSION bump).\n- [ ] Drift-refresh re-sign preserves the same kind.\n## Added (review)\n- The completion signer computes the material fingerprint via the SAME helper plan-review\n  uses (single source of the material field set); it does not redefine the field list.\n\n## Clarification\n- `data[\"kind\"]` is only a ROUTING HINT; the SIGNED `manifest[0]` remains authoritative (114f uses the hint only iff it matches the manifest-derived kind). This story just sets the hint consistently; it does not change what is signed.\n\n## Clarification (review): data[kind] is consumed, not dropped\n- `process_signature` (114f) consumes `data[\"kind\"]` at REDUCE-TIME via its\n  `attestation_kind(manifest, data)` routing (read directly from the event data, validated\n  against the authoritative `manifest[0]`) — it is NOT silently dropped. Additionally, 114f\n  stores the resolved/derived `kind` IN the signature record so the kind is self-describing\n  for consumers (incl. the legacy `signature` mirror).\n- [ ] The signers set `data[\"kind\"]`; the reducer routes by it (validated against manifest[0]) and records the resolved kind in the signature record."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1782796015790750001,"uuid":"b6dbab90-d794-484e-9667-9fb908275408"}